properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 1 at 2:34AM MST until January 1 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...Strong Winds Expected For Wind Prone Locations Into This
Evening...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect until 8 PM MST this evening.

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph.

* WHERE...Central Laramie County, including Cheyenne.

* WHEN...Through 8 PM this evening.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel will be hazardous for
light weight and high profile vehicles, including camping and
tractor trailers. There will be an elevated blow over risk for
area roadways in Central Laramie County, including Cheyenne.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts
of 58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 PM MST THIS EVENING
